---
layout: relation
title:  'obl:tmod'
shortdef : 'temporal modifier'
---

A temporal modifier is a subtype of the [obl]() relation: if the modifier is specifying a time, it is labeled as `tmod`. 
`obl:tmod`, used to attach nouns to predicates when they are functioning as an adverb. 


### Example
ainmneacha a bhí fairsing go maith san ardchathair céad <b>bliain</b> ó shin 'names that were popular enough in the city a hundred <b>years</b> ago
 
 
### Example
Tiocfaidh an Carnabhal go Gaillimh, <b>maidin</b> Dé Sathairn 'Carnaval will come to Galway (on) Saturday morning'


### Example

_daoine a mhair na milliúin <b>bliain</b> ó shin_ `people who lived millions of <b>years</b> ago'

~~~ sdparse
daoine a mhair na milliúin bliain ó shin \n people who lived the millions years from then
obl:tmod(mhair, bliain)
~~~
